1
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:06,715
I could do even more, you know.

2
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:09,509
Would that make you feel better?

3
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:44,961
You think this is enough?

4
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,966
I'm not playing games with grades like a kid.

5
00:00:50,258 --> 00:00:51,634
Stop wasting your time.

6
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:57,974
That's not what I meant...

7
00:00:57,974 --> 00:00:59,601
I really want to make things right.

8
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:00,602
Get out.

9
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:02,771
I’ve got nothing to say.

10
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:04,522
Leave now.

11
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:05,273
Lee Howon.

12
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:16,409
Once it’s broken—

13
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:19,204
—it can’t be fixed.

14
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,970
Oh, perfect timing.

15
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:37,972
Come over here.

16
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:39,974
Huh?

17
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:03,748
This project’s a mess.

18
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,626
Look here.

19
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:17,512
You left out the limits and solutions.

20
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:20,306
And the ethical issues too.

21
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:25,520
If you turn it in like this—

22
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:28,398
—what am I supposed to grade?

23
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:33,319
Yeah...

24
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:36,656
I’m sorry.

25
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,287
Do it again and resubmit.

26
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,289
Lee Howon.

27
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:51,754
It’s really over now.

28
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:55,049
I told myself not to care anymore.

29
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,682
But isn't the new professor kinda hot?

30
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,019
Tall and in good shape too.

31
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:09,439
Wait, when's our MT again?

32
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:11,858
Hey! Watch it!

33
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:34,672
Be careful, will you?

34
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:36,591
Thanks.

35
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:43,848
My eyes always followed you.

36
00:03:44,891 --> 00:03:45,767
And my heart—

37
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,852
—it raced on its own.

38
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:56,569
I made some food.

39
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:58,029
Eat before you go.

40
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:00,949
Try some.

41
00:04:50,581 --> 00:04:51,332
Howon...

42
00:04:51,582 --> 00:04:53,209
I can’t take this anymore.

43
00:04:57,088 --> 00:05:00,091
Every time I see you, I just lose it.

44
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:04,887
Just play with me if you want.

45
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,853
You can use me and throw me away.

46
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:20,695
I've been holding back too...

47
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:23,698
But if you keep this up—

48
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:43,259
—I won’t be able to either.
